text.section:
This section does not apply to:
acceptance of service of process;
surplus lines insurance;
a transaction for which a certificate of authority is not required under § 4-101(b) of this title;
reinsurance, as authorized under Title 5, Subtitle 9 of this article;
an adjuster while providing services with respect to a claim under a policy lawfully solicited, issued, and delivered outside of the State; or
the professional services of an attorney at law.

With respect to a subject of insurance resident, located, or to be performed in the State, a person may not in the State directly or indirectly act as an insurance producer for, or otherwise represent or help on behalf of another, an unauthorized insurer to:
solicit, negotiate, or effect insurance or an annuity contract;
inspect risks;
fix rates;
investigate or adjust losses;
collect premiums; or
transact insurance business in any other manner.
